```class Solution {
public:
    int rangeBitwiseAnd(int left, int right) {
        int result = 0;
        while (left <= right) {
            result = result & left;
            left <<= 1;
        }
        return result;
    }
};```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(right - left))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:
The solution uses a while loop to iterate from left to right, performing a bitwise AND operation between the current number and the result, and then shifting the number left by one bit in each iteration. This ensures that the result is updated efficiently and only a constant amount of space is used. The time complexity is logarithmic because the loop stops as soon as the right operand is reached, reducing the number of iterations.

